news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt directs development authorities to make list of farmers eligible for compensation
news.para: Chief secretary Manoj Kumar Singh and DGP Prashant Kumar, who were in Greater Noida, held a closed-door meeting with officials from the district administration and the three development authorities.

news.title: ASK Property Fund, KREEVA & Shapoorji Pallonji to invest Rs 270 crore in housing project in Gurugram
news.para: Bhavin Jain, CIO of ASK Property Fund, said, "With significant equity from KREEVA and partnership with Shapoorji Pallonji Real Estate, this project effectively minimises risk."

news.title: Kanpur metro completes track construction up to Kanpur Central
news.para: In the coming days, the installation of the third rail on the ‘downline' to Kanpur Central will also be completed. Construction of track slabs on the Baradevi-Naubasta elevated section is progressing rapidly.

news.title: Trump Organization leases brand for two new real estate projects in Saudi Arabia
news.para: It will partner with Dar Global, a London-based luxury real estate developer that will lease the Trump brand but fully own and develop the projects in the Saudi capital, Riyadh.

news.title: Bharat Agri Fert & Realty to invest Rs 85 crore in expansion of resort in Palghar
news.para: The expansion is part of the company's strategic vision to position the resort as a venue for destination weddings and corporate events, in line with the Government of India's 'Wed in India' initiative, a company statement said.

news.title: Mysuru: Delay in relocation of Changadi village from MM Hills Sanctuary worries residents
news.para: The state govt constituted a committee headed by then Chamarajanagar deputy commissioner Charulatha Somal and the then MM Hills deputy conservator of forests (DCF) Y Edukondalu to prepare a master plan for their relocation.

news.title: Mumbai Metro 3 completes track laying for BKC-Cuffe Parade
news.para: The 12.5km long Phase I corridor (Aarey-BKC) was inaugurated on Oct 5 and opened for commuters on Oct 7. It has an average ridership of 22,000 per day.

news.title: Delhi government clarifies launch of voluntary disclosure scheme to NGT
news.para: The decision had come following a meeting involving secretary (environment), DJB CEO, and Central Groundwater Authority chairman. A public advertisement was issued in 2014, requesting details from all private and govt entities using tubewells and borewells.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body razes flat with valuables inside during redevelopment work
news.para: The ward officer further added that since the Gawdi family earlier filed a case in the Judicial Magistrate First Class Court at Belapur over certain objections to the redevelopment issue, they alleged that such a hurried demolition of their flat was wrong and not required. This is why the NMMC stop work notice was sent.

news.title: Kolkata metro's orange line link to airport nears completion
news.para: With the construction ready to enter a crucial phase—curving toward the airport—the implementing agency has sought a rejig of the existing traffic block, having built another new stretch of road space for the seamless movement of Kolkata-bound traffic.

news.title: Aditya Birla Group plans to invest Rs 50,000 crore in Rajasthan
news.para: "Across our businesses, we are committed to scale up our investments. I foresee our group investing Rs 50,000 crore in the next few years spanning cement, renewables, telecom and retail," Birla said.

news.title: Guntur civic body to disconnect drinking water connections of tax defaulters
news.para: GMC has also decided to write to discoms to disconnect power supply in case the taxpayers did not come to terms.

news.title: Allahabad HC issues notice to Greater Noida authority's CEO over pending land allotments
news.para: "The CEO, Greater Noida, to show cause as to why the undertaking given by him and as recorded in the order dated Feb 19, 2024, in a previous case has not been followed resulting in individuals approaching this court by separate petitions for the same relief," the bench of Justices Manoj Kumar Gupta and Anish Kumar Gupta said on Nov 28.

news.title: Patna authorities check 167 vehicles to curb illegal sand mining
news.para: The SP said three tractors loaded with sand were seized under the Bihta police station area late on Saturday night.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body to demolish 47 illegal buildings
news.para: The action will affect around 6,500 people. According to KDMC officials, since people live in these buildings, they will first disconnect electricity and water connections before demolishing the structures.

news.title: Karnataka government explore options to reduce burden of 'unsold' affordable homes
news.para: Data shows the govt is in the process of building 45,000 houses at an outlay of Rs 11.2 lakh per house.

news.title: Bengaluru's housing market faces rising construction costs and high interest rates
news.para: Office-bearers of the Confederation of Real Estate Developers Associations of India (Credai) put the rise in construction costs at 11% this year alone. The reason: A steep hike in labour wages and transportation fees.

news.title: GCZMA imposes Rs 39 crore penalty for environmental damage in Siolim
news.para: Despite a challenge by the violator to the cost calculated, the GCZMA upheld its calculation of environmental costs noting that four different ecosystems have been damaged in the property—mangroves, sand dunes, mud flats and salt marshes.

news.title: RWAs demand freehold property rights & separate authority for new Noida
news.para: RWA demanded converting residential land property of Noida Authority from leasehold to freehold, no increase in FAR post-freehold, and establishment of a separate authority for upcoming New Noida, during a meeting with Noida MLA Pankaj Singh over the weekend.

news.title: New insolvency framework to be creditor-led: IBBI chairman
news.para: "We would be happy if less work goes before the NCLT (National Company Law Tribunal)," Mital said, conceding that the adjudicating authority is now over-burdened. He also rooted for a formal group insolvency framework.
